      <description>I am currently a post-doc at the HRI Laboratoryat Kyoto Universityled by Prof. Kanda. Before joining Kyoto University, I studied Bioinformatics, Genome Research and Intelligent Systems at Bielefeld University, University of Helsinki and Aalto University. I received a B.Sc in Bioinformatics and Genome Research in 2009 and a M.Sc. in Intelligent Systems in 2011. After completing my M.Sc., I joined the Applied Informatics Groupand worked on the SocialRobots project on socially assistive robots to promote physical activity for long-term space missions.</description>
